reviews.review_text: ‘81 Greek Run- 2 Best of the run.

THE ULTIMATE SETLIST Maybe its the headphones but after running through all the mixes, I found this to be my favorite. Only one other, very concise and to the point. Well, the SQ coming through my focusrite scarlet studio headphones is f'n butter.

As for the show, if you don't know, now you know. 2 shows ever feature Shsakedown, Bird Song, and Scarlet> Fire. This and 12/31/84. The latter does not have a China Cat> Rider, or Estimated Eyes, or NFA> Wharf Rat...nor Tenn Jed, and I know how this will sound, but an absolute must-hear LL Rain. It is so good. Which jives with what I'll say about the whole show.

Something was in the water, the air, or the lsd, or something was in something. Seriously, the El Paso, is outstanding, the LL Rain, Jerry at his creative peak. Jed is fire. FOTD is just right. 

And we haven't even touched on the huge piles of meat yet. Bird Song, awesome, Shakedown, all timer, China Cat> Rider, for ser all-timer. Jerry must have been an overflowing caldron of goosebumps all night, not riding the edge but taking a running leap off the cliff without a thought to what comes next only for the eagles to swing in and take him to the edge of space. 

When they return from the break, they commence breathing fire. Hot scarlet, real strong transition jam and a FOTM with an especially good last few minutes. They manage to not get too bogged down in noodle land during E Prophet and the final few minutes give way to a really cool and unique intro mini-jam to Eyes. The Eyes is also excellent.

You might see NFA and think, hmm 80s, meh. Mistake. Wharf Rat is just more butter .
